        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10129",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zend_framework",
                        "name": "zend_framework",
                        "displayName": "Zend Framework",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "06\/07\/06 18:36:19: Modified by studio@peptolab.com\n\nPerhaps Zend_Table_Schema? I'd be wary of adding too much functionality to the base class. Perhaps the schema object could accept an instance of an existing table to :-\n\n{code}\n$table = new myTable();\n\n$schema = new Zend_Table_Schema($table);\n$schema->addField('fieldname', array('type' => 'VARCHAR', 'null' => true));\n\n$result = $table->fetchAll();\n{code}\n\nAnd you could use an instance of Zend_Config to import the structure. I would assume a more generic Zend_Config-type object would be passed for an 'exportStructure' method.\n\nI think this would be a very useful addition as long as it's not too driver-specific. For instance, would you pass a generic string for field type, or create a more generic 'VARCHAR' property that can be translated into a specific database field type? That may make code more portable.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zend_framework",
                        "name": "zend_framework",
                        "displayName": "Zend Framework",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-06-21T22:10:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-06-21T22:10:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10192",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I think something of this magnitude should follow the [normal proposal process|http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFPROP\/Home].",
                    "updateAuthor": {
